<p>
The PCoA panel displayes a scatter plot of the samples using PCoA to define point positions. microbePlot 
                   calculates the principal coordinates using vegan's capscale command. Additionally, the percent variation explained
                   by each principal component axis is shown in parentheses. Any principal coordinate may be plotted on the X or Y
                   axes by selecting the appropriate number in the sidebar. The color variable and color options control the 
                   color of the plotted points. See the 'Color' help topic for details.
</p>
<p>
List of major functions:
</p>
<p>
vegan::capscale - conducts constrained Principle Coordinate Analysis
</p>
